# M3 — Tool calls (make-or-break)

**Date:** 2026-06-30
**Sprint label:** NEW
**Default labels:** enhancement, backend
**Status:** drafted

Milestone M3: full tool-call translation in both directions, streaming included.
This is the milestone that makes Claude Code actually usable on the OpenAI path —
its whole loop is tool calls (read file, edit, run bash). Without it you get a
model that can chat but can't do the job. Budget accordingly: this is where most
of the real effort and most of the bugs live, and the subtle part is
**tool_call_id pairing** across the request direction. Depends on M1
(translation) and M2 (streaming). Milestone exit is an end-to-end real task on a
function-calling-capable upstream, validated manually.

## Prompts

